Stadium 1 Gym Leader Castle

The Gym Leader Castle is a series of challenges in Pokémon Stadium 1 where the player challenges each of the Kanto Gyms, the Elite Four, and the Champion from Red, Green, Blue, and Yellow. The cup features two difficulty modes, Round 1 and Round 2.

Every Gym contains three Trainers, followed by the Gym Leader. When the Elite Four are battled, the player will instead battle the four members of the Elite Four, followed by the Rival. If the player loses against any Trainer, they will have to start that Gym, or the Elite Four, from the beginning. The player can choose a different team for each Gym or Elite Four set.

Defeating the Elite Four and Rival will award the player a Pokémon they can transfer to a connected Game Boy game. The Pokémon that can potentially be received are Bulbasaur, Charmander, Squirtle, Hitmonlee, Hitmonchan, Eevee, Omanyte, and Kabuto.

The player can choose to use either a team selected from rental Pokémon, a team consisting of Pokémon from a connected Game Boy game, or a mix of both.

The rules for this challenge are as follows:

  • The player will select three of their six Pokémon to battle with.
  • The opponents' Pokémon will match the level of your highest-level Pokémon. If your highest-leveled Pokémon is lower than 50, the opponents' Pokémon will all be level 50.
  • If one Pokémon on the opposing team is asleep, any moves that can put a second opposing Pokémon to sleep will fail to do so. The player can still inflict a second sleep status on their own party using Rest.
  • If one Pokémon on the opposing team is frozen, any moves that can freeze a second opposing Pokémon will fail to do so.
  • If the player and the opponent both have only one Pokémon left, and one Pokémon uses Selfdestruct or Explosion to knock out both Pokémon, the player who used Selfdestruct or Explosion will lose the match.
  • Two Pokémon of the same species cannot be entered.

Although enemy Trainers' Pokémon can be anywhere between level 50 and 100, the tables below give a level value and stats associated with level 50. This is because a team of entirely rental Pokémon (which you'd be required to use if you were playing on Switch Online, for instance) will face them at level 50. To see what the stats would be at different levels, make a copy of the Inundata Sheets' Stadium sheet and use the "Highest Level Team Member" box on Pewter Gym's section to set the level.

Rival

  • Rental / Registered Team
  • Red, Green, or Blue with Bulbasaur starter
  • Red, Green, or Blue with Charmander starter
  • Red, Green, or Blue with Squirtle starter
  • Yellow if the player lost the Pallet Town battle
  • Yellow if the player won the Pallet Town battle but lost or skipped the first Route 22 battle
  • Yellow if the player won the Pallet Town and first Route 22 battles

  • Rental / Registered Team

  • Red, Green, or Blue with Charmander starter
  • Red, Green, or Blue with Squirtle starter
  • Yellow if the player lost the Pallet Town battle
  • Yellow if the player won the Pallet Town battle but lost or skipped the first Route 22 battle
  • Yellow if the player won the Pallet Town and first Route 22 battles
